1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,500
<i> All units, be advised.</i>

2
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:13,867
<i>Rural Bank of San Isidro,
robbery in progress.</i>

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:14,833
<i> Lara...</i>

4
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:18,033
<i>Get out of there,
SWAT's on the way.</i>

5
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:19,433
<i> Don't mess this up!</i>

6
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,367
<i>- Lara!
- Bobby?</i>

7
00:00:23,433 --> 00:00:25,433
<i> Godmother! Help us!</i>

8
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,200
<i>A cop is driving,
shoot him!</i>

9
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:28,200
<i> Lara!</i>

10
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:30,367
<i> Let me go, I'm begging you.</i>

11
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:31,667
<i>There's a market there,
take that way!</i>

12
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,500
<i> Fulfill our dream, Bobby.</i>

13
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:36,533
<i> Godmother!</i>

14
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:38,033
<i>The robbers scattered money
everywhere.</i>

15
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:39,100
<i> It caused chaos in the street.</i>

16
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,367
<i> Can I go see her now?</i>

17
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,700
<i>I'm sorry, Sir,
but your wife didn't make it.</i>

18
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:02,100
Hey! Boss Tonyo!

19
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,833
- Sir! Let's drink.
- Sir!

20
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:16,400
Sir Tonyo,
whatever you're going through,

21
00:01:16,967 --> 00:01:18,633
this might help.

22
00:02:01,133 --> 00:02:02,833
Grandmother...

23
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,433
I became a cop because I didn't
want what happened to Mom

24
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:09,467
to ever happen again.

25
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:17,200
But now, Godmother Dina is gone.

26
00:02:20,433 --> 00:02:23,767
And once again,
a child has lost their mother.

27
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:27,167
Dear...

28
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:31,933
It's not your fault
your mother died.

29
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,633
And like Dina,

30
00:02:34,767 --> 00:02:38,567
it's not your fault
she died either.

31
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:42,933
Come, let's go visit her.

32
00:02:43,067 --> 00:02:46,167
She'll be happy to see you.

33
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:51,200
What are you doing here?

34
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:55,267
Do you know what she said?

35
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,400
She said she'd only be
gone a moment

36
00:02:57,533 --> 00:02:59,200
because she was
worried about you!

37
00:03:00,433 --> 00:03:04,300
She left because you called her!

38
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:07,433
It's your fault my wife is dead!

39
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:09,600
Godfather, I'm sorry.

40
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:10,900
You killed her!

41
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:12,600
I'm sorry.

42
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:15,667
Why did you even call her,
Bobby?

43
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,700
It was Mom's day off.

44
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:19,000
She should've been at home.

45
00:03:19,133 --> 00:03:22,267
She should've been with us,
not you!

46
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:26,500
I wish it was you who got shot.

47
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,367
I wish it was you who died!

48
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,133
Please forgive me.

49
00:03:31,267 --> 00:03:32,567
Get out.

50
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,167
Leave!

51
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,500
Let's go.

52
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:39,567
You're not leaving?
You won't leave?

53
00:03:39,967 --> 00:03:41,467
Get out!

54
00:03:42,467 --> 00:03:43,733
Leave!

55
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:45,700
Don't ever come back here, okay?

56
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,533
Don't ever come back!

57
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:50,033
Let's go.

58
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:53,000
Get out!

59
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:07,200
Stop!

60
00:04:17,467 --> 00:04:19,467
Put your hands up!

61
00:04:28,633 --> 00:04:31,967
Win or lose in
the upcoming election,

62
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:36,033
all the proceeds from
this film I'm producing...

63
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:38,967
will go to Calabari.

64
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:44,633
My friend Joaquin's city
has been neglected.

65
00:04:44,767 --> 00:04:46,333
Imagine...

66
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:51,000
Two robberies in just two days.

67
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:57,600
Good thing no one died
in the museum robbery.

68
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:03,833
But in the one at the bank...

69
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:12,600
Calabari needs a change
of leadership.

70
00:05:13,733 --> 00:05:17,567
Our fellow citizens
deserve better.

71
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:20,167
And you think that person
is you, Sir?

72
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:25,767
Miss Beautiful, I wouldn't get
into something I can't do.

73
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:27,967
So you're saying you can defeat

74
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:31,433
the incumbent mayor,
Joaquin "El Hepe" Guerrero?

75
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,900
I can and I will.

76
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:38,767
For Calabari.

77
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:48,067
- Good evening.
- Mayor, good evening.

78
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,400
- Good evening to you.
- Good evening to you too.

79
00:06:03,867 --> 00:06:04,833
Good evening, Mayor.

80
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:06,200
Our condolences to you.

81
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:07,500
Thank you very much.

82
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:09,533
Our deepest sympathies.

83
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:11,567
Thank you, Mayor.

84
00:06:12,067 --> 00:06:15,300
Don't worry about your family.

85
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:19,700
I'll be the one to send your
child to school.

86
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:21,667
Mayor, thank you.

87
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:25,433
I should be the one
thanking you.

88
00:06:25,967 --> 00:06:28,833
Your mom was a true hero.

89
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:31,500
Thank you.

90
00:06:31,633 --> 00:06:33,267
Mayor, please take a seat.

91
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,033
Mayor...

92
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:51,900
- Joaquin.
- What?

93
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:55,600
Victor's saying things
against you again.

94
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:58,867
<i>My friends Joaquin's city is
being neglected.</i>

95
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,533
<i>That Calabari needs
a change of leadership.</i>

96
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:06,800
<i>That our people deserve better.</i>

97
00:07:08,067 --> 00:07:11,600
Here, you handle giving this
to your guys.

98
00:07:11,733 --> 00:07:13,700
For now, I'll call you again
soon

99
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,800
when your next move is ready.

100
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:18,033
Okay?

101
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:19,633
Boss...

102
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:20,900
This is so small.

103
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,600
You are giving us a small amount
this time.

104
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:24,400
Small?

105
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,500
Didn't you hand out some
of the money to the people?

106
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,033
- There.
- Boss...

107
00:07:31,167 --> 00:07:32,233
If we hadn't done that,

108
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:34,467
we'd be caught by now.

109
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,633
Just lay low for now.

110
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:41,800
The cops have their eyes on you
after you took one of them down.

111
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:44,400
That lady cop was the one
at fault, Boss!

112
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:46,467
She just showed up out of
nowhere!

113
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,733
And she wasn't the only one
you killed, right?

114
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,967
What about the woman
you took hostage?

115
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:52,767
She's dead too, right?

116
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,367
Boss, that's not
my fault anymore.

117
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:58,233
I just gave in to her request,
that I let her go.

118
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,067
I was being nice! Right?

119
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,467
Hey, Sonny.

120
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,333
Stop laughing.

121
00:08:05,433 --> 00:08:07,800
The woman you killed was a cop's
wife.

122
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:12,200
I'm sure Tonyo won't stop until
you're caught.

123
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:13,967
Promise me.

124
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,700
- We'll buy that bag, okay?
- Hey, Faye! We're here.

125
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,700
Oh, wait...

126
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:18,833
my parents are here.

127
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:19,300
Bye.

128
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:20,767
Dear!

129
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:21,933
Daddy!

130
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,633
Hello.

131
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:25,633
- Hi, Mommy.
- Hello.

132
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,967
Oh, I alomost forgot.

133
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,500
Where's your amazing brother?

134
00:08:31,633 --> 00:08:34,933
Oh, I think he's in an outreach
program or something.

135
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:36,467
Oh, you see?

136
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,067
Glenn is so great.

137
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,633
He's on an outreach today.

138
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,167
Yes.

139
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:43,967
- Oh, Daddy, Mom...
- What?

140
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,567
My friends are just over here.

141
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,633
I'll go talk to them.

142
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:48,033
- Okay. Sure.
- Excuse me!

143
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:49,767
- Okay.
- Okay. Bye!

144
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:53,333
Okay, so where are we?

145
00:08:57,333 --> 00:08:58,833
Joaquin...

146
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:02,533
What do you think
Victor's game plan is?

147
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:05,500
I mean, you have been in this
position for so long...

148
00:09:05,767 --> 00:09:09,133
why did he think of
challenging you now?

149
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:13,667
I already let him have
the movie world.

150
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:16,633
Now he wants to mess
with politics too?

151
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:22,600
Snakes like him doesn't pick
a time.

152
00:09:22,733 --> 00:09:24,667
Do you want me to call
the media?

153
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:28,600
So you can address all
the things he's been saying?

154
00:09:29,667 --> 00:09:32,800
Glenn has a clean image
with the media.

155
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:35,000
If he speaks on my behalf...

156
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:37,033
Don't involve your son.

157
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:40,133
He might be
the one to ruin me.

158
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,667
Let Victor say
whatever he wants.

159
00:09:50,167 --> 00:09:52,533
He'll get what's coming to him
from El Hepe.

160
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:36,000
Lara, I promise you...

161
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:42,367
I'll find the one
who did this to you.

162
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:52,967
I'll find them.

163
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,833
Our condolences, Tonyo.

164
00:11:09,867 --> 00:11:11,500
You know ...

165
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:16,567
even when Lara snapped at us
for bugging you,

166
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:19,933
she still lent us
her hair dryer.

167
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:22,533
It's so sad she's gone.

168
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:29,467
We're here for you, Tonyo.

169
00:11:32,133 --> 00:11:34,000
Thank you.

170
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,167
Bok...

171
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:51,533
my condolences.

172
00:11:51,667 --> 00:11:53,167
Thank you.

173
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:58,567
- How are you?
- Tonyo! Tonyo!

174
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,700
They say a celebrity's arriving!

175
00:12:01,367 --> 00:12:03,033
What are you doing?

176
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:04,467
I'm not a celebrity.

177
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,667
I just look like one.

178
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,167
I'm a cop, I worked with her.

179
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:09,833
Not you.

180
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:11,267
We just look alike.

181
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:14,033
Tonyo, Boss is coming.

182
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,733
- What?
- Yes.

183
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:27,533
What?

184
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:30,200
You want to join the team
investigating

185
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:32,500
the San Isidro bank robbery?

186
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:33,700
Yes, Sir.

187
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,533
You mentioned I'd be transferred

188
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:37,133
to the investigation group soon.

189
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:40,867
That was before the bank
robbery, Sergeant Enriquez.

190
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:42,900
Sir...

191
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:45,467
You broke a lot of protocols.

192
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,500
Your transfer is on hold

193
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:50,600
while we conduct
an internal investigation.

194
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:53,933
Sir, I was just doing my duty
as a police officer.

195
00:12:54,067 --> 00:12:56,800
I tried to stop the robbers.

196
00:12:56,933 --> 00:12:58,033
And at what cost?

197
00:12:58,167 --> 00:12:59,933
Your godmother's life?

198
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:02,933
She's not the only one
whose family is mourning

199
00:13:03,067 --> 00:13:06,233
because of you,
Sergeant Enriquez.

200
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:08,767
Do you even know another
casualty in that robbery?

201
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:11,167
Lieutenant Conde's partner

202
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:13,067
from Station 12.

203
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,233
And guess what?

204
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:16,233
She was pregnant!

205
00:13:31,333 --> 00:13:33,767
I just got the news.

206
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:39,700
My condolences, son.

207
00:13:49,267 --> 00:13:53,233
I'm not your family,
you don't need to sympathize me.

208
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:05,667
Oh, Sir, oh...

209
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:08,200
Lieutenant Garcia,

210
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:10,733
I worked with Lieutenant Conde.

211
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:12,567
You two know each other?

212
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:15,433
I knew his wife.

213
00:14:15,567 --> 00:14:17,467
I was her client at the bank.

214
00:14:18,133 --> 00:14:19,633
Oh.

215
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:22,633
Would it be okay
to take a selfie?

216
00:14:22,767 --> 00:14:25,033
Oh, sure, sure.

217
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:28,000
There.

218
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:30,400
One, two, you're my idol, Sir.

219
00:14:31,767 --> 00:14:35,033
Would you like coffee? Water?

220
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:36,367
What do you prefer?

221
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,167
Just coffee, please.

222
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,300
- All right.
- Thank you.

223
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:43,333
Oh, it's from...

224
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:03,533
Ouch! What's your problem?

225
00:15:03,667 --> 00:15:04,633
Are you mad?

226
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:05,700
- Hey, fix it!
- Fix it.

227
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:07,667
Calm down, all right?

228
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:08,967
- That's the captian,
- I'm going to be crippled

229
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,900
- because of you.
- Relax.

230
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:12,267
- That's captian.
- Oh, wait.

231
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,167
Why?

232
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,267
What did you say?
Who wants to be a patroller?

233
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,867
Me, Captain.

234
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,300
He's just copying me.

235
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:20,767
What do you mean copying?

236
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,100
You only rushed your application

237
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:24,133
when you found out
I was applying!

238
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:25,633
Come on.

239
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:28,100
Why do you even want
to become a village patroller?

240
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,233
- That's right,
- That's right,

241
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:30,300
- why do you want to be
- why do you want to be

242
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,500
- a village patroller?
- a village patroller?

243
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:34,100
So you can have your own
personal bodyguard, Captain.

244
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,333
Don't believe her.

245
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,333
Oh my, stop bothering me.

246
00:15:37,467 --> 00:15:39,233
You just want to be near Bobby.

247
00:15:39,367 --> 00:15:40,867
- There!
- You got it!

248
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,667
- You nailed it, Captain!
- Captain...

249
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,233
we'll walk you to
and from your house.

250
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:51,067
Boss Idol...

251
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:53,733
What's wrong?

252
00:15:53,867 --> 00:15:55,333
What happened?

253
00:15:57,033 --> 00:15:58,133
Grandmother...

254
00:15:59,633 --> 00:16:02,667
Someone else died because of me.

255
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:06,367
The bank teller,

256
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:09,400
Lieutenant Conde's girlfriend.

257
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:11,433
What?

258
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:15,067
She was pregnant.

259
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:17,233
Pregnant?

260
00:16:57,867 --> 00:16:59,033
Bok...

261
00:16:59,167 --> 00:17:01,000
again, I'm sorry for your loss.

262
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,600
Don't worry.

263
00:17:04,733 --> 00:17:08,333
I'll do everything I can
to solve your wife's case.

264
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:15,267
Why?

265
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:18,333
Are you handling the case?

266
00:17:18,867 --> 00:17:20,400
Bok...

267
00:17:20,533 --> 00:17:22,300
Chief's orders.

268
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:24,433
What do you want me to do?
Disobey him?

269
00:17:24,567 --> 00:17:26,400
She was my wife, Bok.

270
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:29,900
I should be the one handling
her case, not you.

271
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:33,400
Bok...

272
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:37,233
I don't want us
to fight over this.

273
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:42,567
I have no problem with you,
Garcia.

274
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:45,667
But if I don't get this case,

275
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,367
then we'll have a problem.

276
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:52,133
Sorry, Bok.

277
00:17:52,267 --> 00:17:54,300
If it were up to me,

278
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:57,200
I'd say you're the one who
should be on this case.

279
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:53,100
<i>I'm not your family,
you don't need to sympathize me.</i>

280
00:18:56,300 --> 00:19:01,967
<i>I hope one day
you'll forgive me, son.</i>

281
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:06,700
Major...

282
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:10,133
I want those criminals
behind bars.

283
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:16,367
The public might think we are
neglecting them.

284
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:19,667
We're already on it, Mayor.

285
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:23,533
Those criminals
happy day's are over.

286
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:26,900
Major!

287
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:29,167
Major!

288
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:32,367
Lieutenant Conde...

289
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,167
You're still
on bereavement leave.

290
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:36,867
You don't need to report
to the station.

291
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:38,300
Conde...

292
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:42,367
Your girlfriend died, right?

293
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:46,967
My deepest condolences.

294
00:19:48,067 --> 00:19:49,867
I swear...

295
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,700
Those criminals will pay.

296
00:19:56,567 --> 00:19:58,933
You gave the case to Garcia?

297
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:04,300
No one else should
handle it but me!

298
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:07,367
Conde...

299
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:12,767
It's better to give the case
to someone else.

300
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:14,867
Trust Garcia.

301
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,567
And I know you.

302
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:19,500
You wouldn't hold back
on those criminals.

303
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:23,133
They murdered my wife, Major!

304
00:20:23,867 --> 00:20:26,067
And I understand your anger.

305
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,400
But in investigations...

306
00:20:28,133 --> 00:20:30,000
we don't act out of anger.

307
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:31,867
You know that.

308
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:36,367
Conde, you're grieving.

309
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:40,167
Why not give yourself
time to mourn?

310
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,633
If you won't help me find

311
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:46,100
my wife's killer,

312
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:48,767
I'll do it myself.

313
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:51,167
Conde!

314
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:54,567
I won't let you take the law
into your own hands.

315
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:58,833
You're suspended until
you're ready!

316
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,967
Fine. Okay.

317
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,967
Right.

318
00:21:10,233 --> 00:21:13,533
Garcia, I'm begging you.

319
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:18,400
Let me have the people
who killed my wife.

320
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:21,400
They're already
expected in hell.

321
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:36,467
<i>My life would lose all direction
if I lost you.</i>

322
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,500
<i> Well then, don't worry...</i>

323
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:40,933
<i>because I'm not going anywhere.</i>

324
00:21:54,667 --> 00:21:58,233
Boss, I noticed you're sitting
there all alone.

325
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,333
Maybe you'd like
someone to talk to

326
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:03,200
so you won't get bored?

327
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,467
Go ahead, take your pick.
What are you into?

328
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,767
There they are, look.

329
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:08,133
Come closer, Girls,
come on.

330
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:09,100
There.

331
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:11,533
What? Is this okay?

332
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:15,133
All right.

333
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,067
Oh.

334
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:18,600
Oh, what?

335
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:20,233
Well then, you know what to do.

336
00:22:20,367 --> 00:22:22,133
Sit down and keep him
entertained.

337
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:24,100
Introduce yourselves,

338
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:25,967
go on.

339
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:31,067
Hi, I'm Tuesday.

340
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:33,700
Hi.

341
00:22:33,833 --> 00:22:35,667
And I'm Libay.

342
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:40,300
Order something if you want,
okay?

343
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:46,933
Go ahead, just order.

344
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:48,200
Where is Tuesday?

345
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,467
Oh, what were you doing?

346
00:22:50,633 --> 00:22:52,300
You're late again.

347
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:55,000
Look, she's already
talking to someone.

348
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:56,900
Don't worry.

349
00:22:57,033 --> 00:23:00,367
I'll let you know once
she's free later, okay?

350
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:02,000
Okay?

351
00:23:02,133 --> 00:23:03,200
Just relax.

352
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:05,367
All right,
place your orders now.

353
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:16,467
Oh, my dear,
I prepared some snacks.

354
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,100
Eat up.

355
00:23:18,233 --> 00:23:19,800
Thank you, Grandmother.

356
00:23:19,933 --> 00:23:23,033
You know, I'm just
glad you didn't attend

357
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:26,067
the funeral of
Lieutenant Conde's girlfriend..

358
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:29,233
Otherwise,
they might've blamed you.

359
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:32,000
They have every right
to blame me.

360
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,600
Hey!

361
00:23:34,733 --> 00:23:36,867
Why are you blaming yourself?

362
00:23:38,133 --> 00:23:40,733
A lot happened that day.

363
00:23:40,867 --> 00:23:43,733
Don't pin all that on yourself.

364
00:23:43,867 --> 00:23:45,567
Stop that.

365
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,200
Come on.

366
00:23:47,333 --> 00:23:49,700
Come on, let's just watch
something instead, all right?

367
00:23:49,833 --> 00:23:53,767
That might shake off all that
self-pity.

368
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,567
What are you watching,
Grandmother?

369
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:57,333
Look.

370
00:23:57,467 --> 00:24:00,300
A documentary about your idol,
Boss.

371
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:03,200
- His movies are on now.
- What?

372
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:04,633
<i> What?</i>

373
00:24:04,767 --> 00:24:07,667
<i> You children of a duck!</i>

374
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:20,400
Those robbers in the movie...

375
00:24:21,467 --> 00:24:24,033
they're just like the ones
who held up the bank.

376
00:24:24,533 --> 00:24:26,233
Is this gonna take long?

377
00:24:26,367 --> 00:24:27,500
Yes.

378
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:29,300
The discussion's still
pretty heated.

379
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:31,700
Problem with you
is you always show up last.

380
00:24:33,767 --> 00:24:35,600
What?

381
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:41,967
Boss, can I borrow
my girlfriend for a second?

382
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,233
Is he your boyfriend?

383
00:24:46,367 --> 00:24:48,633
That's not my boyfriend.

384
00:24:51,867 --> 00:24:52,867
Come here.

385
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,400
I don't want to go with you.

386
00:24:54,533 --> 00:24:55,533
Come here!

387
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:59,933
Dude, don't force her
if she doesn't want to go.

388
00:25:03,533 --> 00:25:05,167
What did you say?

389
00:25:06,967 --> 00:25:09,233
I said...

390
00:25:09,667 --> 00:25:13,067
don't force the girl
if she doesn't want to go.

391
00:25:13,467 --> 00:25:14,867
Bro, this guy is so arrogant!

392
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:16,400
Hit him! Do it!

393
00:25:16,533 --> 00:25:17,933
Do it!

394
00:26:10,767 --> 00:26:13,100
Hey, stop!
Stop that! Now!

395
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:15,533
Hey, that's enough!
Come on, hurry!

396
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:20,233
Stop it! You don't want to?

397
00:26:21,700 --> 00:26:23,600
Bro, grab it, now!

398
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:30,233
That's enough.

399
00:26:33,533 --> 00:26:36,633
You really are the spring roll
queen of Station 12.

400
00:26:36,767 --> 00:26:37,700
Of course.

401
00:26:37,833 --> 00:26:39,500
Just stay out of my methods,
okay?

402
00:26:39,633 --> 00:26:41,467
Unless, you want
to go up against me?

403
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:44,500
They used your masks during
the bank robbery.

404
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:47,733
Which means the group
that robbed the museum

405
00:26:47,867 --> 00:26:49,133
and the one that robbed
the San Isidro Rural Bank...

406
00:26:49,267 --> 00:26:50,767
they're the same.

407
00:26:57,500 --> 00:26:59,000
That's enough!
We're police officers!

408
00:26:59,133 --> 00:27:00,267
Stay out of this!

409
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,667
Lieutenant Conde?
